            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, combine the <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>rice vinegar</strong> with 75ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[130ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> – this is your <strong>hoisin sauce</strong></p><p>Once the chicken has browned, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>hoisin sauce</strong></p><p>Cook, covered, for a further 8-10 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened - this is your <strong>Chinese chicken</strong></p>",
